<paragraph id="905E36FFFFF0BD5A1FE9AAEA9373056B" blockId="15.[178,1086,925,1035]" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">
: sternite VII with weakly concave posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="08DA2A7AFFF0BD5A1C5DAAE9939B02D3" box="[883,958,925,947]" captionStart="Figs 44-48" captionStartId="15.[178,218,779,799]" captionTargetBox="[196,1048,218,767]" captionTargetId="figure-2@15.[178,1091,212,768]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 44-48: Orsunius cuneatus nov.sp. (44-46) and O. heissi nov.sp. (47-48): (44) male sternite VII; (45, 47) male sternite VIII; (46, 48) posterior portion of male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 44-45, 47: 0.2 mm; 46, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
) oblong and with relatively broad posterior excision of shallowly semi-circular shape (
<figureCitation id="08DA2A7AFFF0BD5A1CF0AACE941402B0" box="[990,1073,954,976]" captionStart="Figs 44-48" captionStartId="15.[178,218,779,799]" captionTargetBox="[196,1048,218,767]" captionTargetId="figure-2@15.[178,1091,212,768]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 44-48: Orsunius cuneatus nov.sp. (44-46) and O. heissi nov.sp. (47-48): (44) male sternite VII; (45, 47) male sternite VIII; (46, 48) posterior portion of male sternite VIII. Scale bars: 44-45, 47: 0.2 mm; 46, 48: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305073/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="08DA2A7AFFF0BD5A1E0FAAAC91B3028E" box="[289,406,984,1006]" captionStart="Figs 36-43" captionStartId="14.[178,218,1484,1504]" captionTargetBox="[192,1078,212,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-2@14.[178,1091,212,1474]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 36-43: Orsunius cuneatus nov.sp. (36-39) and O. heissi nov.sp. (40-43): (36, 40) habitus; (37, 41) forebody; (38, 42) aedeagus in lateral view; (39, 43) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 36- 37, 40-41: 1.0 mm; 38-39, 42-43: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5305071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5305071/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">Figs 42-43</figureCitation>
) small, 
<quantity id="57199B1AFFF0BD5A1EDFAAAC9275028D" box="[497,592,984,1006]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="476" unit="mm" value="0.33">0.33 mm</quantity>
long; internal sac with a pair of broad-based curved apical structures and with a pair of slender basal structures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D8FB6574FFF0BD5A1F9CAD6E935D05C5" pageId="15" pageNumber="476" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="905E36FFFFF0BD5A1F9CAD6E935D05C5" blockId="15.[178,1085,1050,1189]" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">
Comparative notes: In addition to the slightly more distinct punctation of the head and the more densely and coarsely granulose punctation of the pronotum, 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D7CFFF0BD5A1B0AAD4C90CE050B" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orsunius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heissi">
<emphasis id="A295EAEDFFF0BD5A1B0AAD4C90CE050B" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">O. heissi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the evidently closely related 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D7CFFF0BD5A1D85AD219318050B" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" box="[683,829,1109,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orsunius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosus">
<emphasis id="A295EAEDFFF0BD5A1D85AD219318050B" box="[683,829,1109,1131]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">O. granulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D7CFFF0BD5A1C5BAD2193D7050B" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" box="[885,1010,1109,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orsunius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuneatus">
<emphasis id="A295EAEDFFF0BD5A1C5BAD2193D7050B" box="[885,1010,1109,1131]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">O. cuneatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the posterior excision of the male sternite VIII and by the morphology of the aedeagus (shapes of the ventral process and of the internal structures).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D8FB6574FFF0BD5A1F9CADC0940E0588" pageId="15" pageNumber="476" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="905E36FFFFF0BD5A1F9CADC0940E0588" blockId="15.[178,1085,1204,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="476">
